The paper deals with information theory and cryptography, which are both subfields of computer science. The focus is on the wire-tap channel, which is a communication channel with a wire-tapper who tries to intercept the communication. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. However, the paper also deals with the security of the communication, which is a topic in Cryptography (cs.CR). The use of random coding constructions and hash functions suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Coding Theory (cs.CC) and Signal Processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to Multimedia (cs.MM) since secure communication is important in multimedia applications such as video conferencing and streaming.
